If you using the default style, then maybe this is the reason:

[here](https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-shell/blob/master/data/theme/gnome-shell-sass/_common.scss#L683)
```
 .ws-switcher-active-up, .ws-switcher-active-down {
    height: 50px;
    background-color: $selected_bg_color;
    color: $selected_fg_color;
    background-size: 32px;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .ws-switcher-box {
    height: 50px;
    border: 1px solid transparentize($osd_fg_color,0.9);
    background: transparent;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
```

ws-switcher-box (for not active workspaces) has a 1px border, so 50+1+1 = 52px height, 

but ws-switcher-active-up/down (for active workspace) hasn't this border, so only 50px height.

